[[sn:Tsukahara Kofun (Shima)]] [[ja:塚原古墳 (志摩市)]] [[sn:sukahara Kofun (Shima)]]
<!--Tsukahara Kofun (Shima)--><!--Tsukahara Kofun (Shima)--><!--Tsukahara Kofun (Shima)-->

[[File:Tsukahara Kofun (Shima) Artifacts.JPG|thumb|250px|right|{{center|burial goods}}{{small|The Gamontai Kanshōnyū Divine Beast Mirror is a Shima City-designated cultural property. Displayed at the {{ill|Shima City Historical and Folklore Museum|ja|志摩市歴史民俗資料館|qq=draft|qq=draft}}.}}]] '''Tsukahara Kofun''' (塚原古墳) was a circular Kofun (円墳) located in {{ill|Shima City|ja|志摩市|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, {{ill|Daiocho|ja|大王町|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, Nakiri, Tsukahara, {{ill|Mie Prefecture|ja|三重県|qq=draft|qq=draft}}.
A sibling mirror of the {{ill|Gamontai Kanshōnyū Divine Beast Mirror|ja|画文帯環状乳神獣鏡|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, similar to those unearthed from the {{ill|Inariyama Kofun|ja|稲荷山古墳 (行田市)|qq=draft|qq=draft}} in {{ill|Gyoda City|ja|行田市|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, {{ill|Saitama Prefecture|ja|埼玉県|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, the {{ill|Hachiman Kannonzuka Kofun|ja|八幡観音塚古墳|qq=draft|qq=draft}} in {{ill|Takasaki City|ja|高崎市|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, {{ill|Gunma Prefecture|ja|群馬県|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, and the {{ill|Yamanobo Kofun|ja|山ノ坊古墳|qq=draft|qq=draft}} in {{ill|Shintomi Town|ja|新富町|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, {{ill|Miyazaki Prefecture|ja|宮崎県|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, was excavated here.
* '''Excavated Artifacts''' ** Gamontai Kanshōnyū Divine Beast Mirror (1 piece) ** Three magatama (curved beads) made of agate ** 22 tubular beads ** 345 glass beads
The Tsukahara Kofun was destroyed between the late Meiji and Taisho periods. It is estimated to have been about 20 meters in diameter and 3 meters in height, and it is believed to have served as the tomb of a local village chief.
== Cultural Properties == === Shima City Designated Cultural Properties === * '''Tangible Cultural Properties''' ** Gamontai Kanshōnyū Divine Beast Mirror (archaeological artifact) - Stored at the {{ill|Shima City Historical and Folklore Museum|ja|志摩市歴史民俗資料館|qq=draft|qq=draft}}. Designated on December 6, 1996.<ref>[https://www.city.shima.mie.jp/topics/1494470255038.html Shima City Cultural Properties] (Shima City Official Website).</ref>
