{{Infobox ancient site|location={{ill|Shima|qid=Q338009}}|architectural_styles={{ill|circular kofun|qid=Q11394747}}}}{{afc comment|Wikidata entry [[Category:Has wikidata]][[d:Q11428409]] Wikidata name: [[User:Immanuelle|Immanuelle]] ([[User talk:Immanuelle|talk]]) 10:06, 11 June 2025 (UTC)}} [[File:Tsukahara Kofun (Shima) Artifacts.JPG|thumb|250px|right|{{center|burial goods}}{{small|The Gamontai Kanshōnyū Divine Beast Mirror is a Shima City-designated cultural property. Displayed at the {{ill|Shima City Historical and Folklore Museum|ja|志摩市歴史民俗資料館|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shima City Historical and Folklore Museum|qq=|1=Shima City Museum of History and Folklore|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q11490924}}.}}]] '''Tsukahara Kofun''' (塚原古墳) was a circular Kofun (円墳) located in [[:en:Shima, Mie|Shima City]], [[:en:Daiō, Mie|Daiocho]], Nakiri, Tsukahara, [[:en:Mie Prefecture|Mie Prefecture]].
A sibling mirror of the {{ill|Gamontai Kanshōnyū Divine Beast Mirror|ja|画文帯環状乳神獣鏡|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Gamontai Kanshōnyū Divine Beast Mirror|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}}, similar to those unearthed from the [[:en:Inariyama Kofun|Inariyama Kofun]] in [[:en:Gyōda|Gyoda City]], [[:en:Saitama Prefecture|Saitama Prefecture]], the [[:en:Hachiman Kannonzuka Kofun|Hachiman Kannonzuka Kofun]] in [[:en:Takasaki|Takasaki City]], [[:en:Gunma Prefecture|Gunma Prefecture]], and the {{ill|Yamanobo Kofun|ja|山ノ坊古墳|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Yamanobo Kofun|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}} in [[:en:Shintomi, Miyazaki|Shintomi Town]], [[:en:Miyazaki Prefecture|Miyazaki Prefecture]], was excavated here.
* '''Excavated Artifacts''' ** Gamontai Kanshōnyū Divine Beast Mirror (1 piece) ** Three magatama (curved beads) made of agate ** 22 tubular beads ** 345 glass beads
The Tsukahara Kofun was destroyed between the late Meiji and Taisho periods. It is estimated to have been about 20 meters in diameter and 3 meters in height, and it is believed to have served as the tomb of a local village chief.
== Cultural Properties == === Shima City Designated Cultural Properties === * '''Tangible Cultural Properties''' ** Gamontai Kanshōnyū Divine Beast Mirror (archaeological artifact) - Stored at the {{ill|Shima City Historical and Folklore Museum|ja|志摩市歴史民俗資料館|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shima City Historical and Folklore Museum|qq=|1=Shima City Museum of History and Folklore|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q11490924}}. Designated on December 6, 1996.<ref>[https://www.city.shima.mie.jp/topics/1494470255038.html Shima City Cultural Properties] (Shima City Official Website).</ref>
